cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the challenges in developing natural and effective Spoken Dialogue Systems (SDSs) for healthcare, specifically for those living with dementia. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. The paper also discusses the importance of considering the needs of older and cognitively impaired users, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential use of artificial intelligence (AI) in improving SDSs, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the need for a systematic study of interactional patterns in conversation, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
